0c:00.0 Ethernet controller: VMware VMXNET3 Ethernet Controller (rev 01)
13:00.0 Ethernet controller: VMware VMXNET3 Ethernet Controller (rev 01)
1b:00.0 Ethernet controller: VMware VMXNET3 Ethernet Controller (rev 01)



-------------------------

we have backage named (biosdevname ) used in making kernal see the names of interfaces comming from bios and make apply to it.

---------------------------------

to return to naming like eth0 we must lock biosdwvname in booting the machin:

1- when the machine is booting and menu entry appers click e 

2- go to line linux16

3- at the end of line linux16 add (biosdevname=0 net.ifnames=0)


------------------------------------------------------

 to stop and disable NetworkManager :

systemctl stop NetworkManager.servece

systemctl disable NetworkManager

systemctl start network

systemctl enable network



 
 


 





